  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a color override for a single entry in a font color palette.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontPaletteOverride` specifies a replacement color for one slot in a font's color
palette. Use it with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments.PaletteOverrides> to substitute
specific palette entries when cloning a typeface, without replacing the entire palette.

The `Color` field is an `SKColor` value packed as `0xAARRGGBB`. The `Index` field
identifies which slot in the palette to override.

This is a value type (struct) and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Override palette entry 0 with a custom red, then clone the typeface.
var overrides = new SKFontPaletteOverride[]
{
    new SKFontPaletteOverride { Index = 0, Color = (uint)SKColors.Crimson },
};

var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    PaletteIndex = 0,
    PaletteOverrides = overrides,
};

using var customFace = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
